column31: ➕ With so many cases of anaphylaxis after the new vaccines, it's good to know what anaphylaxis is, and how it was discovered. ➕ Anaphylaxis is a severe, potentially life-threatening allergic reaction. It can occur within seconds or minutes of exposure to something you're allergic to, but can also occur hours later. Anaphylaxis causes your immune system to release a flood of chemicals (histamine, basophils, mast cells, and other substances) that can cause you to go into shock — your blood pressure drops suddenly and your airways narrow, blocking breathing. Signs and symptoms include a rapid, weak pulse; a skin rash; and nausea and vomiting. Common triggers include certain foods, vaccines, some medications, insect venom and latex. Many people don’t know the story about how anaphylaxis was first discovered. Literally meaning “without protection”, anaphylaxis was coined by Charles Richet in 1902, who later won the Nobel Prize for his discovery. Richet and professor Paul Jones Portier accidentally discovered anaphylaxis on a marine expedition in the Atlantic after vaccinating dogs with toxins. The two French scientists immunized dogs via injections with a local anemone and jellyfish toxin, and were surprised to discover that upon subsequent injections with even smaller doses of toxin, the dogs experienced a violent reaction and died, whereas they tolerated their initial injection without distress. Thus instead of inducing tolerance (prophylaxis), when lethal responses resulted from previously tolerated doses, he coined the word anaphylaxis – without protection. He was subsequently awarded the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine. Richet proposed the name “aphylaxis” (derived from the Greek: a, contrary to + phylaxis, protection), which was changed to “anaphylaxis” because “aphylaxis” lacked euphonic expression. Their appreciation of uncovering a new phenomenon was described as the outcome of “administration of a substance insufficient to kill or even sicken a normal animal that produces fulminating symptoms and death in an animal previously inoculated with the same substance.” They would later understand this initial injection was sensitizing the animal and priming their immune system for allergic response upon subsequent injection. Full post: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/what-is-anaphylaxis/

column31: When you ingest aluminum, your body will absorb less than 1 percent of it. However, when aluminum is injected into muscle, for example, in a vaccine, your body absorbs 100 percent. The aluminum adjuvant is adsorbed to the antigens and are there to alert your immune system: to cause cellular damage. Without the adjuvant, the antigens (pieces of protein) would do nothing. Vaccines cause prolonged inflammation because of the aluminum. Thus, it's NOT excreted quickly, because then the vaccine would not “work”. In total, American children end up getting about 6,150 mcg of aluminum if they get all of the recommended vaccines on the childhood vaccine schedule. Pro-vaccine advocates will tell you that aluminum is rapidly excreted. But we have the research that shows otherwise. Rabbit studies show almost all of the aluminum (78 to 94 percent) is retained 28 days after intramuscular injection. Autopsy examinations revealed the aluminum accumulated in the kidneys, spleen, liver, heart, lymph nodes, and brain — in that order. Long-term, aluminum also collects in your bones. Studies on human infants show that no aluminum is excreted short term at all. Two-month-old infants were given a total of 1,200 mcg of aluminum in the form of three intramuscular vaccines, as per the standard vaccination schedule. Blood and urine levels of aluminum were measured over the following 12 hours. The authors were "reassured" to find no rise in blood levels of aluminum following vaccination. But no aluminum came out through the urine either. So where did it all go? Suzanne Humphries wrote to one of the authors to get an answer to that question, the author, Dr. Tammy Movsas, wrote back saying: "So... we don't really know what happens to the aluminum at this point in time. As you said, more research is needed in this area." Yet this study is one of the studies used to calm fears that aluminum may be harmful. Excretion of aluminum is not as efficient in infants and young children, yet this fact is almost never taken into consideration. That which is not excreted ends up accumulating in various organs, including the child's brain, kidneys, and bones. (@drmercola ) Study: Movsas 2013

column31: Did you know your cerebral spinal fluid (CSF) is continually produced, and all of it is replaced every six (6) to eight (8) hours! The fluid is eventually absorbed into the veins; it leaves the cerebrospinal spaces in a variety of locations, including spaces around the spinal roots and the cranial nerves. It's one of the most conductive tissues/fluids and it will steal minerals from your bone and adrenal if it's deficient. Magnesium is an essential cofactor for many enzymatic reactions, especially those involved in energy metabolism. Deficits of magnesium are prevalent due to inadequate intake or malabsorption and due to the renal loss of magnesium that occurs in certain disease states (alcoholism, diabetes, autoimmune) and with drug therapy (diuretics, aminoglycosides, cisplatin, digoxin, cyclosporin, amphotericin. Magnesium deficiencies in humans and animals have shown results in neurological disturbances, including hyperexcitability, convulsions and various psychiatric symptoms ranging from apathy to psychosis, some of which can be reversed with magnesium supplementation, others requiring correction of the dysregulation mechanism. In some studies the reduction of cholesterol is quite significant even with modest amounts of magnesium (400-800 mg per day) usually as a supplement. column31: "I can't eat salads everyday, I'll become resistant to lettuce!" That sounds silly, right? We know that healthy foods remain beneficial to us over time, even when we eat them often. Our bodies continue to need their vitamins, minerals, and other beneficial compounds. Herbs are foods. They are not drugs. We do not become resistant to their benefits, and we do not need to stop using nutritive herbs or reserve them only for "special" times. It's a good idea to use a variety of herbs, just like we eat a variety of foods, so we can get a bunch of different benefits. But there's no reason to be concerned that we shouldn't use an herb too long because we'll end up "resistant."

column31: Drainage and detox are not the same thing, yet they are often thought of as synonymous. Drainage is a multi-organ dependent process of ALLOWING the release of substances such as waste and toxins. While detox is the actual process of removing them. Drainage can be thought of as pre-tox. Phase 1. What happens when we detox without proper drainage? A lot of toxin reabsorption ➜ leading to unnecessary Herxheimer Reaction aka a healing crisis, as well as lowered immunity, hormone imbalance, fatigue, aches/pains, dental issues, digestive concerns, emotional/mood ups and downs to name a few. Furthermore, you are more susceptible to all the concerns that come from having a heavy toxin load. Here are the drainage pathways and channels of elimination ... +The Glymphatic System (the brain “lymph”) +The Lymphatic System +The Liver (and gb) +The Lungs +The Kidneys +The Skin +The Blood +The Colon This is a very critical operating system for your body. If you have blockage, flow issues and stagnancy in one system, we see a cascading effect in others. When we sleep, we brain drain in the most literal sense, our brain squeezes and releases, moving glymphatic fluid around cerebral centers where it picks up amyloid protein, pathogens and quells inflammation. This glymphatic fluid drains downward into the lymphatic system through lymph vessels in the head and neck. Along with its associated vessels and nodes , lymph fluid circulates critical immune cells and toxins —to be delivered to the liver. The liver is our number 1 detoxification organ! It pushes over 70% of toxins into our bile which it stores in the gallbladder. Because bile production is very costly, requiring lots of energy, bile is often reabsorbed, as well as the bi-products it contains. The liver additionally drains into the colon and kidney. The kidney process waste through their nephrons and maintain hydration of the colon. column31: In Australia, it is called Infanrix Hexa. Administered at 2, 4 and 6 months of age. It is a Hexavalent Vaccine (6 in 1 combo). 》Diptheria, Tetanus, Pertussis, Hepatitis B, Polio, Haemophilus influenzae type B. No baby would ever be exposed to all of this at one time 💔 Cases of sudden infant death have occurred within 1 to 7 days of a hexavalent vaccine in patients with normal nervous system development. “We examined a large number of sudden infant death syndrome victims in order to point out a possible causal relationship between a previous hexavalent vaccination and the sudden infant death. We selected 110 cases submitted to in-depth histological examination of the autonomic nervous system and provided with detailed clinical and environmental information. In 13 cases (11.8%) the death occurred in temporal association with administration of the hexavalent vaccine (from 1 to 7 days). In none of these victims congenital developmental alterations of the main nervous structures regulating the vital functions were observed. We hypothesize that vaccine components could have a direct role in sparking off a lethal outcome in vulnerable babies. In conclusion, we sustain the need that deaths occurring in a short space of time after hexavalent vaccination are appropriately investigated and submitted to a post-mortem examination particularly of the autonomic nervous system by an expert pathologist to objectively evaluate the possible causative role of the vaccine in SIDS.” https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24083600:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24083600/

column31: New post on website (links in profile/stories) #scienceisunsettling 💉 Edward Jenner and Smallpox Vaccine Experimentation💉 “To me what is interesting about the story of the first vaccine, is that it was created as a safer alternative to a pre-existing form of inoculation that had severe, sometimes fatal, side effects. Embedded into vaccination’s own conception story are adverse reactions, unethical human experimentation, and as a result widespread vaccine refusal. And yet, this information is not commonly passed on in stories told about Edward Jenner, the English scientist and physician widely known for inventing the world’s first vaccine against smallpox. While so many attribute only a positive narrative to Jenner, what’s not often discussed is that his own son became mentally handicapped throughout these repetitious early vaccine experiments. vacca is latin for cow We avoid the ethics question altogether (but not when it comes to Wakefield!). We ignore the experiments gone wrong. We conveniently forget that this earliest form of vaccination involved literally taking one person’s bodily tissues, scab and pus and putting it into an open wound in another person’s arm, sometimes an infant, sometimes an infant who was just born–just to see what would happen, with no regard or attention for long-term safety. The vaccine Jenner would be known for took the pus and scab material from a cow pox sore (vacca is latin for cow), as opposed to an actual smallpox sore or scab from an infected person. Vaccination, therefore, was an attempt at making a safer alternative to variolation, however still risk-filled it was. #edwardjenner #smallpox #smallpoxvacinne 👉🏼 https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/edward-jenner-and-smallpox-vaccine-experimentation/

Here’s why. The senses can help take us “out of our heads” and transport us to the NOW, away from dwelling on regrets from the past &/or concern over the future. Or hug it if you’re so inclined! 🌳 I find this to be a wonderful practice that lifts my spirit anytime. column31: The campaign "This is our shot" is very clever. It means two things: this is our v@xxyne, and this is our chance. In terms of the v@xxyne, it evokes a sense of belonging and community. It's "ours." Each of ours, all of ours. We're doing it for each other. We're doing it together. When someone gets theirs, they feel like they have contributed to and are a good member of the community. Since humans like to be praised, thought positively of, and belong, this is a powerful psychological motivator. The use of "our" also erases the individual. It's not "my shot." It's "our shot." We're not supposed to think about what it can do for us as individuals; we're supposed to think about the greater community impact only. Collectivism at work. They've completely abandoned the neutral "the shot." That doesn't belong to anyone. People are more likely to get it if they think it belongs to them, it's personal. They've been doing this for years with others shots.... (This is in direct contrast to the fact that the shot has not been shown in clinical trials to prevent transmission, meaning it's not really benefiting the community at all.) The second level is, "this is our chance." We've been told since the beginning this was the only way to get back to normal. People are tired of this. Even people who believe that we need to stay home, mask, etc. are tired of it. This is supposed to be the chance to finally get rid of all those restrictions -- eventually -- and have that normal we crave. There will be heavy social pressure to "do your part." If you don't cooperate, you'll be part of the 'out group.' You'll be someone who doesn't want to let us get back to normal. You'll be that kid in school who always goofed off in class that led to the teacher punishing everyone. (At least in some circles.) This is what they want. They have been studying this for months. They chose this slogan carefully. They want everyone to feel pressured to "do their duty." They want people to feel a sense of pride in taking action, and not ask too many tricky questions. In short: they are trying to manipulate you. Will it work?

column31: A message from our owner and lead herbalist: In 2007, when I was still in college, I began working as a therapist for kids with autism. I'd been fascinated by autism since the late 90s -- when it was still relatively rare (compared to today). As I worked with these families, I attended a conference, read books, and listened to their stories. They told me about DAN! doctors, and GF/CF diets, and...vaccines. They told me they had noticed a change, after. Prior to this I had not thought much about vaccines. I had always assumed they were not fun, but were important. When I had gotten cats in early 2006, I took them to the vet to be vaccinated, because that's what responsible people do, right? But I was pregnant with my oldest then. A little wary. I made a promise to myself: I would wait one year before I made a decision. I would not do any vaccines until I had written down, and then answered, all of my questions. I thought, then, that I would still do DTaP, MMR, polio...all the 'big' ones...just later and spaced out. After my daughter was born in early 2008, I spent *every* time she was sleeping, reading. I wrote down dozens of questions and sought answers. I read through the CDC's Pink Book, the WHO position papers, articles by Dr. Russell Blaylock, and a handful of peer-reviewed studies. (There weren't as many as there are now!) By the end of that year...there was NO WAY I was ever going to get vaccines for any of my kids. Not.a.chance. And I haven't. I don't regret it. My oldest kids know a little bit now and they're happy that I chose not to, as well. They've been pretty healthy kids, for the most part. Zero sick visits (in almost 13 years, 6 kids). Zero antibiotics. Zero other prescriptions. Just the occasional cold or tummy bug. And chicken pox, which they sailed through. I would encourage any new parent to do what I did -- wait. Ask questions. Read. And read some more. Wait until you feel fully confident in your decision. You can always start...but you can't undo it. There's so much more information out there now and so many more places to find it. It's one of the biggest and most important decisions you'll ever make for your child. It deserves serious time and attention. We hope this story helps someone!

column31: Today marks two years since baby Zedikiah died just 6 days after the 2 month vaccines.💔 please keep his family in your thoughts and prayers today. Shared from his mama: “Zedikiah was born 09/27/2018. Minus a lot of pregnancy complications for me, he was perfectly healthy. 5lbs, 15.5 oz, 18 inches long. Zedikiah attended a 3 day visit after birth, his 2 week newborn screening, and was up to date thus far. We took Zedikiah to his doctors appointment on 12/10/2018 where he was now weighing in at 9 lbs, 2 oz’s, 21 inches long, head circumference 15. He was on the 1 percentile for his weight and 30 percentile for his height. He was small, but perfectly healthy (neither of us, mom or dad or big). He received his two month vaccinations. He received DTAP-HIB-IPV (documented 3 times), PCV 13, ROTAVIRUS, HEP B. Zedikiah seemed perfectly fine, with just the usual crying they say babies will have. We did not need to give Zedikiah medicine as he did not develop a fever. Leading up to the day of his passing, Zedikiah seemed a little more sleepier and didn’t poop since the day he received his shots. That evening was a regular evening. I get home about 6:00pm from work and take over. Zedikiah and I played for a bit, I fed him and changed him, then we played some more. Zedikiah eventually got tired so we laid him down. Kiah did not like sleeping on his back and could not fall asleep that way so we would lay him on his stomach and pat his back. He fell asleep about 9:00pm. Dad and I just hung out for a bit, watching movies until about 1:00am. We checked on Kiah before we went to bed and he was sleeping so peacefully. All through the night I kept tossing and turning. Something was telling me to check on Kiah. I looked over at him and he appeared to be sleeping so I fell back to sleep. My alarm woke me up at 7:30am to get ready for work. I got up and grabbed Kiah as I always do to make his bottle and his body was stiff, cold, and blue. I screamed so loud. His dad and I screamed and called the police. It was horrific. I will never forget that horrible day. Full post: https://circleofmamas.com/mama-stories/sudden-death-6-days-after-2-month-shots/

column31: The hidden history of the polio vaccine, and it's other disasters. The Cutter Incident: In April 1955 more than 200,000 children in five Western and mid-Western USA states received a polio vaccine in which the process of inactivating the live virus proved to be defective. Within days there were reports of paralysis and within a month the first mass vaccination programme against polio had to be abandoned. Subsequent investigations revealed that the vaccine, manufactured by the California-based family firm of Cutter Laboratories, had caused 40,000 cases of polio, leaving 200 children with varying degrees of paralysis and killing 10. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1383764/ Full 68 pages here: https://www.globalhealthchronicles.org/files/original/60703b72ad384b1f569b2767ea848f2a.PDF Within days there were reports of paralysis and within a month the first mass vaccination programme against polio had to be abandoned. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1383764/?fbclid=IwAR3ZT7JFt_foyZAS66J3rPCcG3iwM95G3CU_QNYBRwbY-k26V7lS-IcUsxA SV40, the cancer causing virus from the contaminated polio vaccine. Millions of people worldwide were inadvertently exposed to live simian virus 40 (SV40) between 1955 and 1963 through immunisation with SV40-contaminated polio vaccines. Although the prevalence of SV40 infections in humans is not known, numerous studies suggest that SV40 is a pathogen resident in the human population today. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/m/pubmed/15202523/:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15202523/ The young scientists feared that DNA from the SV40 virus alone could trigger cancers. Some 35 years later their fears began to appear well founded when SV40 DNA turned up in human cancers. https://www.smh.com.au/national/deadly-shots-the-polio-vaccine-saga-20041023-gdjz1z.html In this regard, the hypothesis that rhesus monkeys have not been used for vaccine production since the early 1960s when it was discovered that they were often infected with SV40 is incorrect. Presently, in China, 50% of oral attenuated poliovirus vaccines are still prepared in primary rhesus monkey kidney cells. https://cancerres.aacrjournals.org/content/65/22/10273 Studies with laboratory animals indicate that maternal-infant transmission is one possible route of SV40 spread. This may represent a pathway for SV40 infections in humans (of unknown frequency), as there are reports of the detection and expression of SV40 T-ag and the presence of viral DNA in cases of primary brain cancers in infants and young children. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC452549/ SV40 has been found in every type of primary paediatric brain tumour examined. http://www.sv40foundation.org/Bradford-Hill.html:=:https://www.sv40foundation.org/bradford-hill/ Millions given infected polio vaccine: https://www.smh.com.au/national/millions-given-infected-polio-vaccine-20041023-gdjz32.html?fbclid=IwAR0_vxh0UT93Bd0lXErMRgbF7pYT1UhwaXj-fheusVZmb93ma0mQ4HsEubM How The Oral Polio Vaccine Can Cause Polio https://www.npr.org/2019/11/16/780068006/how-the-oral-polio-vaccine-can-cause-polio?t=1597571117960&fbclid=IwAR1jjaNzF_i1kttmOH0S23xmkEJnLjXhZ-oUm4t2p-P19BxXTAQLuyVDbf0 The Polio Vaccine. http://vaxtruth.org/2012/03/the-polio-vaccine-part-2-2/?fbclid=IwAR0ZoC3NGPGL2u8xl87k5suP9xkLJcnpz4TWF5KnoVF1rTlL4ADysjtHdi8 Vaccine-induced paralysis calls for action, says study. https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/vaccine-induced-paralysis-calls-for-action-says-study/article24740588.ece?fbclid=IwAR1E9DSMFwZ1RjTpeIS9dSG60AYTXy9wsudu8GuESapudqvo7ibedSUSHPc Mutant Strains Of Polio Vaccine Now Cause More Paralysis Than Wild Polio. https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2017/06/28/534403083/mutant-strains-of-polio-vaccine-now-cause-more-paralysis-than-wild-polio?t=1596477232843&fbclid=IwAR3IRUh45GKLLk-ucVEX4KB1fHRxR1MCpdAHOdOKMMn1lj5mxTLWkHGn_gc Correlation between Non-Polio Acute Flaccid Paralysis Rates with Pulse Polio Frequency in India. https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6121585/pdf/ijerph-15-01755.pdf?fbclid=IwAR2VMhKVMLwr6U8fOlbkc-q9dTgS87BoECmYcobIHues8G2UDh55Jt_C5Qg Is India actually free of polio? column31: "But we would never have eradicated disease like polio if it wasn't for vaccines"? The question we always hear. "When the polio vaccine came into use in 1955, polio was officially defined as being caused by poliovirus, an enterovirus that had circulated freely through our gut since ancient times. Unlike other diseases that vaccines get the credit for fixing, the first serious US polio outbreak occured in 1894, there was a major epidemic in 1916, then things got worse in the 30s, 40s and early 50s. What could have caused this mysterious appearance at a time when mortality from other infectious diseases had declined a great deal? Pesticides, lead arsenate and DDT, interacting with a virus or viruses, is a strong candidate. It is possible the pesticides were damaging nerves, allowing the entry of normally-harmless enteroviruses. The evidence does show the polio vaccine eliminated outbreaks of polio associated with poliovirus in the US and other countries. However, before the vaccine, polio was usually diagnosed without a pathology test for poliovirus – it was common for doctors to diagnose ‘poliovirus’ so patients could get health funding. Therefore other enteroviruses besides poliovirus may well have been causing poliomyelitis, or polio may have been simply caused by pesticides without the involvement of a virus (although the fact that polio vaccines lead to many cases of paralysis does point to the involvement of a virus). These considerations have ramifications that continue today, in both developed nations where there are still outbreaks of paralysing “polio-like” illness and in third-world nations. After vaccination was introduced in 1955, a strict pathology test was required to confirm a patient had polio. Also, at this point the definition of polio changed—paralysis had to last for 60 days instead of just 24 hours, and non-paralytic cases were no longer called polio. These factors lowered the number of polio cases significantly, making it look like the vaccine was very successful. We should also note the book ‘Silent Spring’, which was influencial in DDT use in agriculture being banned, came out in 1962. http://vaxinfostarthere.com/did-vaccines-save-us/?fbclid=IwAR0IdRwjEzpRDoQ8lBcNp648Hz1Cq1yk3Da4-yfLP90YVikfXSuRz9HLd1U Dissolving Illusions by Dr Suzanne Humphries goes deep into the history of disease, detailing the timeline of many (with documented research papers) so we can see that they were actually on the decline BEFORE the advent of the vaccine. Chapter 'The Disappearance of Polio': http://www.whale.to/c/DissolvingIllusions-Polio.pdf?fbclid=IwAR0OUhGdd8NAkKpKpcHNiLbpLKjNEsp_UKTcjJJwjNpRGZFWyQC6FLXm8e4 The paralysis that was blamed on the poliovirus in the 1940s and 50s, could it be because of the widespread chemical/pesticide spraying of DDT, a highly toxic (now banned) pesticide? Health departments, along with chemical companies, were encouraging the spraying of DDT on the public. Mass DDT spraying campaigns took place on beaches, aerially over swimming pools and parks — especially during the summer months (aka farming season). Coincidentally most “polio” paralysis cases happened during the summer months and in children. Parents were even encouraged to spray their children directly with the highly toxic chemical as well as put it in baths and other places where children had direct contact with DDT. People including children were getting “sprayed” with DDT to get rid of head-lice and other lice. The DDT was affecting the nervous system of the body. The vaccine came out around the same time that they stopped “spraying” DDT everywhere and on everyone, hence polio started to disappear. In the mid-1940s, scientists began to alert the government and Congress that DDT spraying was causing a huge increase in paralysis and nervous system damage. But the government, on the back of World War Two, couldn’t admit their mistake — a mistake that would have cost them MILLIONS in damages through lawsuits from those affected. Someone then had the brilliant idea to quietly start exporting DDT instead of spraying, slowly ban DDT as not to cause alarm and promote a “solution” in the form of the polio vaccine: https://youtu.be/fw4i5IfDtPI:=:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fw4i5IfDtPI&feature=youtu.be Polio increased with introduction of DDT & started declining before the polio vaccine was introduced: https://www.westonaprice.org/health-topics/environmental-toxins/pesticides-and-polio-a-critique-of-scientific-literature/ Suzanne Humphries, MD, speaking on Polio at the Association of Natural Health Conference: https://youtu.be/Twch-T-n8Ns:=:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Twch-T-n8Ns&feature=youtu.be What about Polio? https://m.youtube.com/watch?feature=youtu.be&v=aNw5SD3txBU&fbclid=IwAR0rt3aLp1ZbrXwUjH6ndCOfY3L7 The real history of Polio: https://realnewsaustralia.com/2019/02/27/the-real-history-of-polio-20-things-you-didnt-know/ Science did not have technology to differentiate between polio and other entero and...

column31: TH1 & TH2 A balance of Th1/Th2 cells in the body is defined as immunostasis (or immune balance) and is required for optimum health and wellness. In Natural Immunity, for example exposure to chickenpox, Th1 response externalizes the infection and provides permanent immunity. In Vaccine-Induced Immunity, Th2 response internalizes the infection because the Immune System was forced into an emergency - based Th2 response and results in poor immune memory. Thus regular vaccine boosters are required throughout life. T cells (thymus cells) are the major cell in the immune system; they direct and control all immune responses as well as immune memory. Subsets of T cells are the T-helper cells (Th). T-helper cells coordinate and direct the safest and most effective immune response. Using Moskowitz’s measles example, we know that, when infected with the measles virus naturally via the nasopharyngeal route, the body produces a Th1 response that externalizes the infection and provides permanent immunity. Fever, rash, coughing, sneezing, etc are signs of the body ridding itself of this infection. Bypassing the normal body lines of defense by injecting a vaccine forces the immune system into an emergency-based Th2 response which serves to internalize the infection. So, if a natural, viral (measles) infection results in a Th1 response, why don’t we make vaccines that could elicit the same response. Natural immune response to a virus externalizes and eliminates it. However artificial vaccine-induced Th2 response drives the infection deeper and allows it to become chronic. Adjuvants are often employed to enhance the development of an efficacious specific response. The problem lies within what type of immune response is happening. TH1 is the cell-mediated immune response that happens after naturally acquiring an infection, and then TH2 humoral kicks in with antibodies and ensures immunity, but, they work in tandom. Vaccination uses adjuvants to stimulate a TH2 response, bypassing the TH1, which puts the immune system into a perpetual state of confusion. This can kick in Autoimmunity for predisposed individuals (See the medical textbook “Vaccines and Autoimmunity” by world renowned immunologist Dr. Yehuda Shoenfeld MD). The vaccination process itself destroys immune capacity by overstimulating the humoral TH2 immune response while never engaging the cell-mediated TH1 immune response. The immune system then stays in a state of agitation, which leads to all sorts of chronic health problems, injury and death. And, never confers immunity (e.g., booster shots are required to create more antibodies - the only measurement of "vaccine effectiveness"). On the other hand, when a child naturally gets an infection a proper TH1 immune response occurs, and then TH2 kicks in, tags the antigens with antibodies and we now have immunity. No need for booster shots. "What people don't know about vaccines, what most doctors don't know, but well demonstrated in medical literature, is that vaccines shift your immune system to an immune suppression type of state called the "TH2 shift." That's what most vaccines do. They shift your immune system to a weaker, antibody type immune system. If you're injecting people with so many vaccines that you’re keeping them in this constant state that now you’re switching everyone to this TH2 immune suppression, then everyone becomes more susceptible [to infectious diseases] and no one is talking about that. Now, a lot of scientists know that, but they are afraid to speak out because their careers would be ruined." column31: Histamine intolerance is a relatively new health ailment on the scene, but it can be a very serious thing for some people. Histamine is a substance that is stored in our cells. It can be released during times when we’ve had an allergic reaction or if there is inflammation present in the body. Histamine is either stored in the body in mast cells — which are a type of white blood cell — or dissolved by enzymes that eat up histamine. It functions in the body in a variety of ways that include: -Protecting against infection. -Regulating the digestion of proteins. -Regulating sleep and the function of your mind. Diamine Oxidase (DAO) is the enzyme that is responsible for the deactivation or storage of histamine. When the body loses its ability to properly produce DAO then histamine intolerance arises. There are many things that can contribute to the body’s loss of ability to produce adequate DAO. The body is usually able to handle the elimination of histamine. But, when the body can’t, it becomes overloaded and then many different symptoms can manifest. There are many ways histamine intolerance can manifest in the body. If you notice any of the following things occurring — especially if there is more than one — it would be worth exploring whether or not histamine intolerance is a factor for you.

column31: Most women will face a gestational diabetes test somewhere around their 28th week of pregnancy. But do you know all the facts about GD...and the test itself? In America, a two-step test is generally used. A 1-hour "glucose challenge test" with 50 g sugar (or GCT), followed by a 3-hour "glucose tolerance test" with 100 g sugar (or GTT) if the first one is failed. That first test doesn't require fasting, so results can be pretty far off for some women, depending on what else they've eaten that day. Plus, women who usually eat low-sugar or low-carb diets may fail because their bodies aren't used to dealing with a huge load of sugar. A better approach is to look at a woman's risk factors -- being over 25, having a family history of diabetes, being overweight, having a fasting blood sugar higher than 95. A woman without these risk factors doesn't need the test, as she has less than 1% chance of having GD. In most other countries, a 2-hour fasting test with 75 g sugar is used, which is a better approach for at-risk women. It's also worth noting the diagnostic criteria has shifted over time, and there's still no consensus on exactly what numbers qualify a woman as having GD, which can mean there is some under- or over-diagnosis. The glucola drink that women are given is filled with terrible ingredients, and has an immediate negative impact on many women. A lot feel sick and awful during the test, and may vomit -- which negates the test results. Many doctors say there aren't alternatives, but that isn't true. Studies have been done using different forms of candy (Twizzlers and jelly beans) as well as meals calculated to the right amount of carbs. These alternatives were just as good in providing a correct diagnosis, and were tolerated much better. Prevalence of gestational diabetes is increasing, as mothers are heavier and older. In some populations, prevalence is under 2%. In others, it's over 26%, a 13-fold increase. For many women, diet can help control GD. Avoiding sugar and refined carbs makes a big difference. For about 50% of women, they eventually end up needing insulin (the studies weren't clear whether diet changes didn't work or if women didn't want/weren't able to make them -- probably some of both). Interestingly, some studies have been done on using nutritional supplements in women who were diagnosed with GD. They found that magnesium, in particular, was associated with significant reductions in fasting blood sugar, insulin sensitivity, markers of inflammation, and pregnancy outcomes. Newborns were 4x less likely to have jaundice or be hospitalized. Vitamin D and E, calcium, and zinc were all shown to be beneficial as well. The bottom line? Many women could get away with examining their risk factors and checking their fasting blood sugar once to see if they might have GD, and not need any further testing. If testing is needed, healthier alternatives to the 'glucola' can and should be used (and the 2-hr fasting test is better than the 1-hr non-fasting test). Eating healthy and avoiding refined carbs and simple sugars, and getting plenty of magnesium is key. column31: Guys, I talk about the importance of the milieu of tissues and the terrain often. There are so many misconceptions about terrain theory, the one I hear often is terrain theory is simply the opposite of germ theory. Let's not be overly reductionist and boil down terrain theory to 'germs don't matter, only the health of the body matters'. This is a huge misconception. Terrain theory doesn't mean that germs don't cause illness. It means the terrain determines the illness. Let me say that again, especially in these current times; the terrain determines the illness. What does that mean? Our environment- the air we breathe, the water we drink, the food we eat, the thoughts we think, the industrial chemicals we create, bring into our homes and use, the ecosystem we belong to- determine our response to a microbe and the response of the microbe. Remember illness and symptoms of illness whether it be a fever or a sore throat is a response to our environment, it is a necessary reaction for our survival. A fever isn't the illness, it is a response. Recent research found that environmental climate change is making more virulent viruses that cause more severe infections in mammals. The terrain of our earth impacts the germs as well as us. Staph aureus can cause serious infection or be a normal part of the microbiome or be used for treatment in autoimmune disease. The terrain of the body affects the response of the microbes. The antibiotic revolution has led to a devastating microbial situation with antibiotic resistant superbugs lining up for a plague the likes of we've never seen. The terrain will always respond, eradicating microbes without a thought of the downstream effect is shortsighted. The price of our unchecked war on germs is too high. We must put what we've learned under a microscope back into the bigger picture. We must demand a more nuanced approach, more thoughtful way to research and develop a relationship with the microbes that make up our body and our world. column31: Constipation is a condition that many children suffer from in developed countries, with many mothers and pediatricians overlooking the condition. Studies have shown that up to 30% of children in the United States have experienced constipation, and it accounts for over 35% of trips to the gastroenterologist. This condition may be overlooked for the more serious symptoms which may accompany it, such as allergies, eczema and asthma. There are many ways to help with constipation. One way is by adding more good fats and oils to the diet. Oils like coconut and organic olive oil can keep things moving. Try making these “Constipation candies” for your little to make getting their oil in fun! Find the recipe and instructions here - https://mommypotamus.com/constipation-candy/ Learn more about ways to help deal with constipation here - https://modernalternativemama.com/2016/05/09/kids-constipation-normal/

Yes probably - it would mean they would have to dig deep, and review the current legislations - No Jab, No Play, No Jab, no Pay. Those that choose to not vaccinate, are constantly being blamed for ‘outbreaks, even the CDC admits that whooping cough outbreaks cannot be blamed on those choosing not to vaccinate: "vaccinated people are reservoirs for silent infection and become potential transmitters to unprotected infants" and "Therefore, even young, recently vaccinated children may serve as reservoirs and potential transmitters of infection": http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/6/5/00-0512_article:=:https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/404.html?aspxerrorpath=/eid/article/6/5/00-0512_article Virus shedding: ”The term is used to refer to shedding from a single cell, shedding from one part of the body into another part of the body, and shedding from bodies into the environment where the viruses may infect other bodies.” https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Viral_shedding Vaccine strain measles virus detected in urine of vaccinated child 37 days after vaccination. Recently vaccinated individuals can shed the virus, especially the immune compromised. https://jcm.asm.org/content/jcm/33/9/2485.full.pdf?fbclid=IwAR04bUWKoKECF5sj4VSwcZwgOtyjarwdmY434BTfv8KIN8ZqoT4dJ8knYPg In 1991 less than 71% of Australian children were fully vaccinated for whooping cough yet there were only 347 cases, while in 2011 with over 90% fully vaccinated there were over 38000 cases reported. http://www9.health.gov.au/cda/source/rpt_4_sel.cfm 'Public health authorities may be facing a situation similar to that of polio, where vaccinated individuals can still transmit infection' https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4482312/ Did you know that a major source of infection for infants is siblings fully vaccinated against whooping cough? During the peak epidemic period “siblings were the most important sources of pertussis in infants 6 months and younger, particularly fully vaccinated children aged 2 and 3 years…Even if cocooning programs could achieve full vaccination coverage of parents and ensure all siblings were fully vaccinated according to national schedules, waning immunity in siblings could provide a means for ongoing transmission to infants.” https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25391405/ Asymptomatic transmission and the resurgence of Bordetella pertussis: "asymptomatic transmission is the most parsimonious explanation for many of the observations surrounding the resurgence of B. pertussis" https://bmcmedicine.biomedcentral.com/.../s12916-015-0382-8 "Whooping cough resurgence due to vaccinated people not knowing they're infectious" https://www.sciencedaily.com/rel.../2015/06/150624071018.htm "all children who were primed by DTaP vaccines will be more susceptible to pertussis throughout their lifetimes, and there is no easy way to decrease this increased lifetime susceptibility” The 112-Year Odyssey of Pertussis and Pertussis Vaccines—Mistakes Made and Implications for the Future: https://academic.oup.com/.../10.1093/jpids/piz005/5359449... “This disease is back because we didn’t really understand how our immune defenses against whooping cough worked, and did not understand how the vaccines needed to work to prevent it,” said Christopher J. Gill, associate professor of global health. "Instead we layered ASSUMPTIONS upon ASSUMPTIONS, and now find ourselves in the uncomfortable position of admitting that we may made some crucial errors. https://www.bu.edu/.../resurgence-of-whooping-cough-may.../ “Case-patients having received at least 1 pertussis vaccine dose had a higher odds of having PRN–B. pertussis compared with unvaccinated case-patients” https://academic.oup.com/cid/article/60/2/223/2895696 “Although pertussis resurgence is not completely understood, we hypothesize that current acellular pertussis (aP) vaccines fail to prevent colonization and transmission” https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24277828:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24277828/ ”In our view, we are approaching a critical decision point. In the US, pertussis rates and infant pertussis deaths are now at a 70-year high, and despite record uptake of aP vaccines, pertussis rates in the US have continued to rise, casting doubt on whether further increasing aP vaccine coverage can ever compensate for their fundamental limitations” https://f1000research.com/articles/6-1568/v1 Who got sick? The fully & partially vaccinated. column31: Don’t be suspicious, don’t be suspicious! 🎶 Step one for living “free faced” in a masked world! 😄 Here are my REAL tips for showing up w/ a free face: 1️⃣ Don’t be afraid or anticipate negative reactions. Fear is responsible in large part for where we are today. Be confident & friendly. 2️⃣ Don’t get angry or argue if you are hassled or harangued. It gets you nowhere. All the data in the world is unlikely to change a single individual’s mind. 3️⃣ Adopt an attitude of love & compassion. Those around you who make different choices are well-intentioned & acting on what they know or have been told. 4️⃣ Be accommodating or respectful if asked to comply with the request of a family member or employer. See if there is any room for compromise or exceptions. 5️⃣ Own your choice and live joyfully. You are free to live as you see fit. ☀️☀️☀️ PS Not into free faces? These tips might work for you too! (Re-read them & see! 🥰) You might ask why some are making the free face choice, in the first place. I can’t speak for everyone. But from what I can tell, some believe it is their constitutional right to live freely, face uncovered. Others are convinced masks are ineffective. Some just don’t buy the fear-based mainstream narrative & the restrictions that limit our connections & interactions. For me, it’s a combination of all of the above & a sense deep inside me that masks are simply immoral: they de-humanize us on a primordial level, detaching us from one another. Put another way, I believe we were made by God to connect & interact w/ one another with unveiled faces. If you want an idea of why I’m not worried about people catching or spreading c0vid this way, listen to my Wise Traditions podcast interviews w/ @zachbushmd “Proactive amidst this crisis” or Dr. Andy Kaufman “Are germs the enemy?” P.S. column31: Never heard of this drug? It's in most OTC cough formulations. But...is it safe or effective? Dextromethophan is considered one of the "better" cough medicines in terms of efficacy, but a large study showed that it reduced coughing by about 17%. (Every other effect was due to the soothing of the syrup or placebo effect.) It works by crossing the blood-brain barrier and acting on the central nervous system, to basically force your body to stop coughing. Even though you are still sick, and may need to cough to get rid of the germs. Because of its actions on the CNS, this drug has been abused by kids because it produces a "high" if taken in large amounts. It's not recommended to be used by anyone under 6, although despite all these issues, remains freely available. Our assessment? Better to skip this one. Sources: https://americanaddictioncenters.org/dextromethorphan-dxm https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5601090/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3562553/ https://www.drugs.com/sfx/dextromethorphan-side-effects.html https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4985807/...:=:https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4985807/.../ https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/comp.../Dextromethorphan...

column31: You know, I wish provaxxers looked critically at their own studies that they believe to prove their own point. [take for example the meta-analysis, “Vaccines are not associated with autism: An evidence-based meta-analysis of case-control and cohort studies”, by Luke E. Taylor, published 2014] For example, the idea that vaccines are not associated to [insert your favorite adverse reaction here], is currently not strongly supported by any of available science that I’ve seen. Let’s take the most popular one of all, that ‘vaccines are not associated to autism’. If you were to try to support that with studies, you’ll likely be linking study after study that shows: MMR is not associated to autism Thimerosal is not associated to autism Here’s the problem with those studies in terms of design: you’re comparing a vaccinated population vs a vaccinated population, but using the MMR as a variable. As an exaggeration, let’s assuming the following vaccination histories of the case and control group: Case Group Hep B x 3 DTaP x 4 Hib x 3 Pneumococcal x 3 Polio x 3 Influenza x 1 Varicella x 1 Hep A x 1 MMR x 1 Control Group Hep B x 3 DTaP x 4 Hib x 3 Pneumococcal x 3 Polio x 3 Influenza x 1 Varicella x 1 Hep A x 1 The only difference being that the case group has been vaccinated for MMR and the control group has not. When you find that the autism rate between both groups is statistically insignificant, you then conclude that MMR is not associated to autism. Fair enough, so as long as the PROPER CONTEXT of this conclusion is established, that is, if you’re going to be vaccinating anyways, then the MMR isn’t going to pose any more significant risk. But for the life of me, I DO NOT UNDERSTAND how people use these studies designed in this manner to conclude that VACCINES are not associated to autism. You want to attack Exley and Shaw, fine. But if you’re going to do that, you should be just as upset with the multitude of studies that don’t even come CLOSE to answering the question, are vaccines (as a whole) associated to [adverse reaction]? Full post: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/vaccine-autism-pseudoscience/ also in stories Guest post: whyser #autism

JUST IN CASE you still believe we can trust the FDA to ensure that a vaccine is actually “safe and effective” before it is licensed for use in this country, I implore you to read the following, about our pertussis/whooping cough vaccines:

💡 Have you ever been told by your doctor that the pertussis vaccine (the “p” in DTaP & Tdap) can make you an asymptomatic carrier of whooping cough?

In 2013, an FDA study was published due to concern over the rising rates of whooping cough, which looked at the effectiveness of current acellular pertussis vaccines (DTaP & Tdap). 

It was titled, “Acellular pertussis vaccines protect against disease but fail to prevent infection and transmission in a nonhuman primate model.”

What they did, was take two animals and vaccinate them with the pertussis vaccine. They placed them in an enclosure with an unvaccinated animal, then introduced to the group, another animal which had been infected with pertussis. What they found, is that while the two vaccinated animals presented no symptoms of whooping cough, they both became infected with pertussis bacteria, to the same degree of bacterial colonization as the unvaccinated animal.

They then hypothesized that vaccinated subjects who were infected with pertussis, could potentially transmit the bacteria to other subjects.

To test this, they took two vaccinated animals, infected them with pertussis, and placed them in separate cages. An unvaccinated animal was then introduced to each cage. Their hypothesis was confirmed. Both of the unvaccinated animals contracted pertussis from the asymptomatic, vaccinated animals.

Their conclusion? Due to the lack of symptoms, the number of vaccinated individuals who contract and transmit pertussis is unknown, and this failure of the pertussis vaccine is likely to be responsible for the resurgence of cases of whooping cough in the United States.

But there’s more.

Several other important studies have been published which support these findings.

A 2015 study focused on parents who attempt to “cocoon” their newborn babies by requesting that all relatives be vaccinated in order to protect their infants from whooping cough.

Their conclusion? It doesn’t work.

A 2014 study sought to determine which individuals were transmitting whooping cough to infants six months or younger. It was found that FULLY vaccinated siblings, aged 2-3 years, were the most important sources of infection for infants.

Research published in 2014 on the development of a live pertussis vaccine, plainly states, that, “acellular pertussis vaccines do not control pertussis”.

All of these findings are proven over and over again, by the outbreaks of whooping cough in populations with near-complete vaccine coverage or in fully vaccinated populations.

For example, the most recent pertussis outbreak in LA County last year, consisted of 90 cases. Every single one of those 90 individuals who had contracted whooping cough, had been vaccinated.

The pertussis vaccines given today have been in use since 1991.

That means it took 22 years and several hundreds of millions of doses of pertussis vaccines administered to infants, children, and adults, before the FDA began to investigate whether the vaccine was actually working to prevent infection, transmission, and outbreaks of whooping cough (in 2013).

It’s now been seven years since that study was published.  

🤔 Why is this information not front page news?

🤔 Why are we not being told that the vaccine is ineffective?

🤔 And why are they still pushing an ineffective vaccine?

👉🏻 Most of us probably already know the answer: No one can know that the FDA, the CDC, and the HHS are pushing ineffective vaccines that put infants at risk…

…Because people might start questioning the entire vaccine program. 

As they should.

🗣 P.S. This doesn’t even cover the evidence of harm from these aluminum-containing vaccines, nor the DTP vaccine which contained both mercury and aluminum, and was in use for *decades* prior to it being discontinued due to a massive amount of lawsuits over it causing severe vaccine injuries. 

👌🏻 AND in case you think we can trust the World Health Organization, just know that despite experts discovering that the DTP is literally killing children in developing nations as we speak (I know a family who lost their healthy 2 month old 10 hrs after receiving it, this past June - it actually increases mortality), the WHO continues to recommend its use in the rest of the developing world while it was discontinued here in the US in the mid 80s.

column31: Most trials can only tease out immediate side effects -- soreness, headaches, fevers, etc. Those are fairly easy because they happen quickly and are obvious. Long-term side effects are much harder to tease out. To find out if there is an actual causal relationship, researchers have to look at extremely large groups of people and follow them for several years (one group who received the intervention and one group that didn't, matched for age, sex, health concerns, etc.), and then see if certain diagnoses are more common in the intervention group than the non-intervention group. It's hard to do studies of this scale in the first place. It's *impossible* on interventions (like the new C-v@x) that haven't been around long enough to have studied anything long term. It's also hard to prove, for sure, that any trends seen, especially if they're still "uncommon," are actually, causally related to the intervention. So, those who have financial and emotional incentives to believe in the intervention, at any cost, simply dismiss these long-term effects as coincidence. It's hard to find enough evidence for them, and it's much more mentally comfortable to see them as coincidence. This, of course, ignores the lived experiences and pleas of those who are unlucky enough to suffer the side effects. We'll see what happens over the next few months....

column31: New moms often worry that their breastfed babies aren’t pooping enough…or that their poop looks weird…or that there’s something else wrong. Typically, these mothers are assured — “If baby is not uncomfortable, it’s fine to go up to two weeks without pooping! Breastmilk is the perfect food so it’s all used up and there’s just no waste left!” Unfortunately, although this bit of advice has been passed around for years, there is not one shred of evidence to back it up. Since how often a breastfed baby poops — and how often s/he should poop — actually affects long-term gut development (and therefore, long-term health), it actually matters a lot if this is true or not. column31: This is one of the issues I have with vaccines: of all the infections with sars-covi2, only a small percent actually develop the severe disease known as covid19, and less than 1%, specifically around 0.2% of total cases will result in death. (Which may itself be transferred from other causes as we have seen all too often). It is estimated 80% are completely asymptomatic. Fauci said 70% of Americans needs to be vaccinated, but you know it’s going to be everyone. Problem is: a larger percent of people will experience 'adverse events' from the vaccine, than they would have from the natural virus. This dilemma reminds me of polio: prior to the vaccine, around 1% of polio virus infections resulted in the severe disease known paralytic polio myelitis. It was not all 100% of infections. And there are reasons for why so many children in the late 1940s and early 1950s suddenly were developing paralytic polio. It was called “provocation polio” and was caused by recent DPT injection, or tonsil surgery. There was research done on this, and I’ve documented this research on my website. But, my point is to prevent the 1% of actual paralytic polio, for example, they decided to create a vaccine for ALL children. (Which caused polio, and also gave an entire generation of children SV-40 virus and hepatitis C) For example, from the Moderna trial results so far: 80% of trial participants experienced at least one adverse event. In the high dose group: 21% reported one or more severe adverse events. A grade 3 severe adverse event is defined as requiring medical attention. 👉🏼 https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/nejmoa2022483:=:https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/nejmoa2022483?cookieSet=1 For the Pfizer vaccines, 92% of trial participants reported a local, systemic reaction, whereas 50% reported an adverse event. 👉🏼 https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.08.17.20176651v1.full.pdf Again, this is all for a virus that really goes unnoticed by the vast majority of people, unless they are already comorbid or vitamin D deficient. column31: Arnica has been used for skincare and anti-inflammatory properties for centuries, since at least the 1500’s. Though it can be toxic in high concentrations ingested, it is a very common homeopathic aid for bruises and swelling today. The active component in arnica is called helenalin. It is possible to be sensitive to helenalin; so if you develop a rash or stomach pain after taking arnica you may be sensitive and should discontinue use. Helenalin is a known anti-inflammatory, and as such, tinctures, pills, balms, and oils of arnica have dramatic anti-inflammatory properties. The fatty acid thymol has also been found in arnica montana, which has known antibiotic properties! Do you use arnica?

column31: Many women, near the end of their pregnancies, are told they "need" to induce labor. Unfortunately, some of the most commonly given reasons are absolute nonsense. "Big Baby" -- Women can and do deliver babies that are 10 - 11 lbs. if they have support, their labors aren't rushed, and they can change positions as needed. Bigger babies may also be stronger and more able to 'help' with the birth. Plus, ultrasound readings are notoriously off, by up to 3 lbs. in either direction. A "big" baby may be a very average 7-lb. baby in the end. "Past due date" -- The range of normal gestational length is much longer than most realize. Doctors like to stick to right around 39 weeks, and some will go up to 41. But a few babies may need until 43 - 44 weeks! Plus, dates can be off. Even a first-trimester dating ultrasound can only date within 1 week, and women with longer cycles may not be as far along as they think, either. As long as baby is moving and doing well, there's no reason to induce. "Low fluid" -- Fluid pockets are very hard to measure once baby is near term, and doctors and ultrasound techs often miss one or more of them. True low fluid is VERY rare. Also, if mom rests and drinks plenty of water, fluid can be replenished. "Small/unproven pelvis" -- Very few women are 'too small' to be able to deliver their baby naturally, if they are able to move around as needed. And 'unproven' is just nonsense, everyone has a first time. A lot of these reasons can be avoided by choosing a care provider who isn't induction-happy and who doesn't push for a highly inaccurate, generally unnecessary third trimester ultrasound. As long as mama and baby are doing well, wait until baby is ready!

column31: Need a dinner idea? Try making this! Directions: -The night before, soak black beans in water (to cover by 1″) with a pinch of baking soda. -The next day, cook the black beans in water until soft, about 45 min. Drain and set aside. -In a 9×13 baking dish, add your rice. -Add stock. -Add tomato sauce. -Then spices. -Add carrots, peas, and black beans. -Stir it all together. -Lay your chicken pieces on top. You can use drumsticks, bone-in breasts, boneless breasts…really whatever you want. Ideally the chicken should be covering most of the rice. If not, lightly cover with foil. -Now, put it in the oven at 350 for about an hour. Then it’s done. If you had beans already cooked and in the fridge or freezer, this dish would seriously come together in 10 minutes. It is a no-brainer! Serve it with shredded cheese, slices of avocado, sour cream, fresh salsa — whatever you like and have on hand. Read more about this awesome recipe here - https://modernalternativemama.com/2012/07/12/recipe-collection-mexican-chicken-and-rice-with-beans/

column31: When we experience chronic stress, our body responds by sending defense signals to the endocrine system, which then triggers the release of various hormones designed to prepare the body for an emergency. In doing that, the hormones, particularly cortisol, also depresses the immune system. Increased levels of cortisol, in fact, can decrease white blood cells and inflammation, while increasing tumor development and growth and the overall rate of infection. This year has been very stressful. Many people feel defeated. Chronic stress can seem overwhelming, and a person may feel unable to regain control over their life. However, there are a number of ways to reduce stress and improve your overall well-being!

column31: After everything that went down this weekend, we're coining a new phrase: "2020'd." That is, something that happened that got all screwed up! And our Black Friday/Cyber Monday sale got *majorly* 2020'd! We're going to tell you the behind-the-scenes story. When we first got started in late 2015, we had no idea if we would even go anywhere. So we spent a weekend putting up a basic website and built it on Wordpress (like half the sites on the internet). It's not intended as an ecommerce platform, but worked just fine...then. By late 2018, we knew that it wouldn't work forever. We would need a new solution to handle the increased business. So we hired some web developers and set out to create one of the best ecommerce platforms ever...from scratch. These things always take longer than you think they will. Our goal had been to have it done by early fall 2020, but it wasn't. And isn't. We knew that going into this time of year on our existing platform was a risk...and it ended badly. The sheer volume of customers trying to order caused it to crash and burn...repeatedly! Our IT team has worked literally round the clock, standing up many new servers, changing settings, and doing everything to get it back up...and the usual tricks just aren't working. Seriously 2020'd! We're working to get it fixed *for real.* (We could use a full-time web developer or two, if anyone's looking for a job....) You guys deserve to have a better shopping experience. We will take care of ALL of you this month. Our customer service team is on it, and we've got some surprises up our sleeve later in the month. We appreciate your patience and understanding as we go through these growing pains. It's a good problem to have, and we will solve it. :)

column6: I believe in informed consent. Always. Vaccines wasn't something I really thought about until I became a mama. Here to share what I have researched along the way. I am a RN.
column31: When looking to find the ingredients for each vaccine i like to go directly to the vaccine inserts. We all have a fundamental right to make our own choices and decisions in regards to what is put into our bodies. Informed consent, always. These are the ingredients in the Quadracel Vaccine (Diphtheria, Tetanus, Pertussis, Polio). Given at 4 years old. Vaccine Insert 👇 https://apps.medicines.org.au/files/swpquadr.pdf Absorbed on 1.5 mg Aluminium phosphate (0.33 mg aluminium). The manufacture of this product includes exposure to bovine materials. 》Diphtheria toxoid is a cell-free preparation of diphtheria toxin detoxified with formaldehyde. 》Tetanus toxoid is prepared by detoxification of tetanus toxin with formaldehyde. 》Inactivated Poliovirus is an enhanced formaldehyde-inactivated product. 》The three poliovirus types are propagated in MRC-5 cells (aborted fetal cells). As with any vaccine, immunisation with Quadracel may not protect 100% of susceptible individuals. No deaths or cases of encephalitis/acute encephalopathy, invasive bacterial infection, infantile spasms or anaphylactic reactions were reported within 48 hours of vaccination. What about after the 48 hours? Seizures, encephalitis, and encephalopathy are all documented adverse reactions following vaccination.
column34: 6 6.1 PHARMACEUTICAL PARTICULARS LIST OF EXCIPIENTS Aluminium phosphate Phenoxyethanol Polysorbate 80 Bovine serum albumin Polymyxin B sulfate Neomycin Formaldehyde Glutaral ater for injections
